            <title>[LUCENE-2060] CMS should default its maxThreadCount to 1 (not 3)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2060</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;From rough experience, I think the current default of 3 is too large.  I think we get the most bang for the buck going from 0 to 1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this will especially impact optimize on an index with many segments &amp;#8211; in this case the MergePolicy happily exposes concurrency (multiple pending merges), and CMS will happily launch 3 threads to carry that out.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
